    94→## 3. Transport Architecture
    95→
    96→Six transport classes were deobfuscated from the minified CLI:
    97→
    98→```
    99→                           ┌─────────────────────┐
   100→                           │  ad1 (ProcessInput)  │  Base: NDJSON parser + control request/response
   101→                           │  - read() generator  │
   102→                           │  - sendRequest()     │
   103→                           │  - createCanUseTool() │
   104→                           └──────────┬──────────┘
   105→                                      │ extends
   106→                           ┌──────────▼──────────┐
   107→                           │  LQA (SdkUrl)        │  --sdk-url mode  ← OUR TARGET
   108→                           │  - PassThrough bridge │
   109→                           │  - transport delegate │
   110→                           └──────────┬──────────┘
   111→                                      │ uses
   112→                    ┌─────────────────┼─────────────────┐
   113→                    │                                     │
   114→          ┌─────────▼─────────┐              ┌───────────▼───────────┐
   115→          │  sd1 (WebSocket)   │              │  kQA (Hybrid)          │
   116→          │  - WS send+receive │              │  extends sd1           │
   117→          │  - reconnect logic │              │  - WS receive only     │
   118→          │  - message buffer  │              │  - HTTP POST for send  │
   119→          │  - ping/pong       │              │  - retry with backoff  │
   120→          └────────────────────┘              └────────────────────────┘
   121→
   122→  Web UI / Remote Sessions:
   123→          ┌────────────────────┐         ┌─────────────────────────┐
   124→          │  MFA (SessionsWS)  │◄────────│  WFA (RemoteSessionMgr) │
   125→          │  - Subscribe WS    │         │  - Permission routing   │
   126→          │  - API auth        │         │  - HTTP POST for send   │
   127→          └────────────────────┘         └─────────────────────────┘
   128→
   129→  Direct Connect (Browser):
   130→          ┌────────────────────┐
   131→          │  fFA (DirectConnect)│  Simplified WS for browser use
   132→          │  - sendMessage()   │
   133→          │  - respondToPermit │
   134→          │  - sendInterrupt() │
   135→          └────────────────────┘
   136→```
   137→
   138→### Transport Selection Logic
   139→
   140→```typescript
   141→function createTransport(url: URL, headers?: Record<string, string>, sessionId?: string) {
   142→  if (url.protocol === "ws:" || url.protocol === "wss:") {
   143→    if (process.env.CLAUDE_CODE_POST_FOR_SESSION_INGRESS_V2) {
   144→      return new HybridTransport(url, headers, sessionId);  // WS receive + HTTP POST send
   145→    }
   146→    return new WebSocketTransport(url, headers, sessionId);  // Pure WebSocket
   147→  }
   148→  throw Error(`Unsupported protocol: ${url.protocol}`);
   149→}
   150→```
   151→
