   154→## 4. Connection Lifecycle
   155→
   156→### Sequence Diagram
   157→
   158→```
   159→  Your Server (WS)                          Claude Code CLI
   160→       │                                         │
   161→       │◄──────── WebSocket CONNECT ──────────────│  (with Auth header)
   162→       │                                         │
   163→       │                                         │──► system/init message
   164→       │◄──────── {"type":"system","subtype":"init",...} ──│
   165→       │                                         │
   166→       │──── {"type":"user","message":{...}} ────►│  (you send first prompt)
   167→       │                                         │
   168→       │                                         │──► LLM processing...
   169→       │                                         │
   170→       │◄──── {"type":"stream_event",...} ────────│  (if --verbose)
   171→       │◄──── {"type":"stream_event",...} ────────│
   172→       │◄──── {"type":"assistant",...} ───────────│  (full response)
   173→       │                                         │
   174→       │  (if tool needs permission)              │
   175→       │◄──── {"type":"control_request",          │
   176→       │       "request":{"subtype":"can_use_tool"│
   177→       │       ,"tool_name":"Bash",...}} ─────────│
   178→       │                                         │
   179→       │──── {"type":"control_response",          │  (you approve/deny)
   180→       │      "response":{"subtype":"success",    │
   181→       │      "request_id":"...","response":      │
   182→       │      {"behavior":"allow",...}}} ─────────►│
   183→       │                                         │
   184→       │◄──── {"type":"assistant",...} ───────────│  (continues after approval)
   185→       │◄──── {"type":"result",...} ──────────────│  (query complete)
   186→       │                                         │
   187→       │──── {"type":"user","message":{...}} ────►│  (next turn, optional)
   188→       │         ...                              │
   189→```
   190→
   191→### Authentication
   192→
   193→The CLI sends authentication via HTTP headers on the WebSocket upgrade request:
   194→
   195→```
   196→Authorization: Bearer <session_access_token>
   197→X-Environment-Runner-Version: <version>  (optional)
   198→X-Last-Request-Id: <uuid>  (on reconnect, for message replay)
   199→```
   200→
   201→**Token sources** (priority order):
   202→1. `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ACCESS_TOKEN` environment variable
   203→2. Internal session ingress token
   204→3. Token read from file descriptor specified by `CLAUDE_CODE_WEBSOCKET_AUTH_FILE_DESCRIPTOR`
   205→
   206→---
   207→
   208→## 5. Wire Protocol (NDJSON)
   209→
   210→Each message is a single JSON object followed by `\n` (newline). Multiple messages can be sent in sequence.
   211→
   212→```
   213→{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Hello"},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":""}\n
   214→{"type":"assistant","message":{...},"session_id":"abc123","uuid":"..."}\n
   215→```
   216→
   217→### Message Categories
   218→
   219→| Direction | Types |
   220→|-----------|-------|
   221→| **Server → CLI** | `user`, `control_response`, `control_cancel_request`, `keep_alive`, `update_environment_variables` |
   222→| **CLI → Server** | `system`, `assistant`, `result`, `stream_event`, `tool_progress`, `tool_use_summary`, `auth_status`, `control_request` (can_use_tool, hook_callback), `keep_alive`, `streamlined_text`, `streamlined_tool_use_summary` |
   223→| **Bidirectional** | `control_request`, `control_response`, `keep_alive` |
   224→
   225→### Filtered by SDK (present on wire but not exposed to consumers)
   226→
   227→These types are present in the NDJSON stream but the official SDK filters them out:
   228→- `control_request` / `control_response` / `control_cancel_request` — handled internally
   229→- `keep_alive` — silently consumed
   230→- `streamlined_text` / `streamlined_tool_use_summary` — internal streamlined mode
   231→
