   560→## 7. Control Protocol (13 Subtypes)
   561→
   562→Control messages use a request/response pattern with correlated `request_id` fields.
   563→
   564→### Envelope Format
   565→
   566→```typescript
   567→// Request
   568→interface SDKControlRequest {
   569→  type: "control_request";
   570→  request_id: string;              // UUID for correlation
   571→  request: ControlRequestPayload;  // discriminated by "subtype"
   572→}
   573→
   574→// Success Response
   575→interface SDKControlResponse {
   576→  type: "control_response";
   577→  response: {
   578→    subtype: "success";
   579→    request_id: string;            // matches the request
   580→    response?: Record<string, unknown>;
   581→  };
   582→}
   583→
   584→// Error Response
   585→interface SDKControlErrorResponse {
   586→  type: "control_response";
   587→  response: {
   588→    subtype: "error";
   589→    request_id: string;
   590→    error: string;
   591→    pending_permission_requests?: SDKControlRequest[];  // queued permissions
   592→  };
   593→}
   594→
   595→// Cancel Request
   596→interface SDKControlCancelRequest {
   597→  type: "control_cancel_request";
   598→  request_id: string;              // request to cancel
   599→}
   600→```
   601→
   602→### 7.1. `initialize` (Server → CLI)
   603→
   604→Register hooks, MCP servers, agents, system prompt. **Must be sent before the first `user` message**.
   605→
   606→```typescript
   607→// Request
   608→{
   609→  subtype: "initialize",
   610→  hooks?: Record<HookEvent, { matcher?: string; hookCallbackIds: string[]; timeout?: number }[]>,
   611→  sdkMcpServers?: string[],
   612→  jsonSchema?: Record<string, unknown>,
   613→  systemPrompt?: string,
   614→  appendSystemPrompt?: string,
   615→  agents?: Record<string, AgentDefinition>
   616→}
   617→
   618→// Response
   619→{
   620→  commands: { name: string; description: string; argumentHint?: string }[],
   621→  output_style: string,
   622→  available_output_styles: string[],
   623→  models: { value: string; displayName: string; description: string }[],
   624→  account: { email?: string; organization?: string; subscriptionType?: string; apiKeySource?: string },
   625→  fast_mode?: boolean
   626→}
   627→```
   628→
   629→**Error**: `"Already initialized"` if called twice.
   630→
   631→### 7.2. `can_use_tool` (CLI → Server)
   632→
   633→**The most important control message.** The CLI asks the server for permission to use a tool.
   634→
   635→```typescript
   636→// Request (from CLI)
   637→{
   638→  subtype: "can_use_tool",
