   905→
   906→## 9. Session Management
   907→
   908→### Session ID
   909→
   910→- Generated by CLI via `crypto.randomUUID()` on startup
   911→- Included in every outgoing message (`session_id` field)
   912→- Stored in global state, accessible via `U6()` internally
   913→- Use for session resume: `--resume <session-id>`
   914→
   915→### Initialization Sequence (Detailed)
   916→
   917→The `initialize` control_request should be sent **before** the first `user` message. The exact sequence is:
   918→
   919→```
   920→Server                                  CLI
   921→  |                                      |
   922→  |<-- WS connect ----------------------|
   923→  |                                      |
   924→  |-- control_request {initialize} ---->|  (optional: register hooks, MCP, agents)
   925→  |<-- control_response {success} ------|  (returns commands, models, account info)
   926→  |                                      |
   927→  |-- user message --------------------->|  (first prompt)
   928→  |<-- system/init ----------------------|  (tools, model, session_id, etc.)
   929→  |<-- assistant ... --------------------|
   930→  |<-- result ----------------------------|
   931→```
   932→
   933→The `initialize` request lets you:
   934→- Set a custom `systemPrompt` or `appendSystemPrompt`
   935→- Register hook callbacks (with `hookCallbackIds` that map to `hook_callback` control requests)
   936→- Register SDK-side MCP server names
   937→- Set a JSON schema for structured output
   938→- Register custom agent definitions
   939→
   940→### Multi-Turn Conversations
   941→
   942→After receiving a `result` message, you can send another `user` message to continue the conversation. Internally, user messages are queued in `queuedCommands` and processed in a loop by the CLI's `c()` function.
   943→
   944→```
   945→Server: {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"First question"},...}
   946→CLI:    {"type":"system","subtype":"init",...}
   947→CLI:    {"type":"assistant",...}
   948→CLI:    {"type":"result","subtype":"success",...}
   949→
   950→Server: {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Follow-up"},...}
   951→CLI:    {"type":"assistant",...}
   952→CLI:    {"type":"result","subtype":"success",...}
   953→```
   954→
   955→**Duplicate detection**: Messages with a `uuid` field are checked against a dedup function. Duplicates are skipped but acknowledged with `isReplay: true` if `replayUserMessages` is enabled.
   956→
   957→**Session end behavior**:
   958→- For single-turn queries: stdin/transport is closed after first result
   959→- For multi-turn (streaming input): CLI keeps running, waiting for more user messages
   960→- The CLI remains alive as long as the WebSocket connection is open
   961→
   962→### Session Resume
   963→
   964→```bash
   965→claude --sdk-url ws://localhost:8765 --print --output-format stream-json --input-format stream-json --resume <session-id> -p ""
   966→```
   967→
   968→When resuming:
   969→1. CLI reads the transcript JSONL file from `~/.claude/projects/<project>/<sessionId>.jsonl`
   970→2. Loads and replays previous messages with `isReplay: true`
   971→3. Sets `sessionId` to the resumed session's ID
   972→4. Then waits for new `user` message
   973→
   974→**Resume at specific message**: `--resume-session-at <uuid>` truncates history to that message.
   975→
   976→### Fork Session
   977→
   978→```bash
   979→claude --sdk-url ws://localhost:8765 --print --output-format stream-json --input-format stream-json --resume <session-id> --fork-session -p ""
   980→```
   981→
   982→When forking:
   983→- A NEW session ID is generated
   984→- The old session's messages are loaded as context
   985→- The new session gets a fresh UUID — this allows branching without modifying the original session
   986→
   987→### Context Compaction
   988→
   989→When the context window fills up:
   990→1. CLI sends `{"type":"system","subtype":"status","status":"compacting"}`
   991→2. After compaction: `{"type":"system","subtype":"compact_boundary","compact_metadata":{"trigger":"auto","pre_tokens":N}}`
   992→3. Then: `{"type":"system","subtype":"status","status":null}` (compacting ended)
   993→
   994→### Result Triggers
   995→
   996→| Result Subtype | Trigger |
   997→|----------------|---------|
   998→| `success` | Normal completion — assistant finished responding |
   999→| `error_during_execution` | Unhandled error during tool execution |
  1000→| `error_max_turns` | Reached `--max-turns` limit |
  1001→| `error_max_budget_usd` | Exceeded USD budget |
  1002→| `error_max_structured_output_retries` | Failed structured output after N retries |
  1003→
  1004→---
  1005→
  1006→## 10. Reconnection & Resilience
  1007→
  1008→### WebSocket Reconnection (sd1 class)
  1009→
  1010→| Constant | Value |
  1011→|----------|-------|
  1012→| Max reconnect attempts | 3 |
  1013→| Base reconnect delay | 1000ms |
  1014→| Max reconnect delay | 30000ms |
  1015→| Backoff formula | `min(1000 * 2^(attempt-1), 30000)` |
  1016→| Ping interval | 10000ms |
  1017→| Circular buffer capacity | 1000 messages |
  1018→
  1019→### Reconnection Flow
  1020→
  1021→1. WebSocket connection drops
  1022→2. CLI attempts reconnect with exponential backoff
  1023→3. Sends `X-Last-Request-Id` header with last sent message UUID
  1024→4. Server should replay messages sent after that UUID
  1025→5. CLI replays buffered outgoing messages from circular buffer
  1026→6. After 3 failed attempts → state = "closed", fires close callback
  1027→
  1028→### Keepalive
  1029→
  1030→- CLI sends `{"type":"keep_alive"}` periodically
  1031→- WebSocket ping/pong every 10 seconds (Node.js only, skipped on Bun)
  1032→- If no pong received before next ping → connection considered dead → triggers reconnect
  1033→
  1034→### Hybrid Transport (kQA) — HTTP POST Resilience
  1035→
  1036→When `CLAUDE_CODE_POST_FOR_SESSION_INGRESS_V2` is set:
  1037→
  1038→| Constant | Value |
  1039→|----------|-------|
  1040→| Max POST retries | 10 |
  1041→| Base POST delay | 500ms |
  1042→| Max POST delay | 8000ms |
  1043→| Backoff formula | `min(500 * 2^(attempt-1), 8000)` |
  1044→
  1045→URL conversion: `wss://host/ws/path` → `https://host/session/path/events`
  1046→
  1047→POST body format:
  1048→```json
  1049→{ "events": [<message>] }
  1050→```
  1051→
  1052→---
  1053→
  1054→## 11. Environment Variables
  1055→
  1056→| Variable | Purpose |
  1057→|----------|---------|
  1058→| `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ACCESS_TOKEN` | Bearer token for WebSocket auth (highest priority) |
  1059→| `CLAUDE_CODE_WEBSOCKET_AUTH_FILE_DESCRIPTOR` | File descriptor to read auth token from |
  1060→| `CLAUDE_CODE_POST_FOR_SESSION_INGRESS_V2` | Enable hybrid transport (WS receive + HTTP POST send) |
  1061→| `CLAUDE_CODE_ENVIRONMENT_RUNNER_VERSION` | Sent as `x-environment-runner-version` header |
  1062→| `CLAUDE_CODE_REMOTE` | Indicates running in remote mode |
  1063→| `CLAUDE_CODE_REMOTE_SESSION_ID` | Remote session identifier |
  1064→| `CLAUDE_CODE_CONTAINER_ID` | Container ID for remote environments |
  1065→
  1066→---
  1067→
  1068→## 12. Transport Class Hierarchy
  1069→
  1070→### `ad1` — ProcessInputTransport (Base)
  1071→
  1072→```typescript
  1073→class ProcessInputTransport {
  1074→  input: ReadableStream;
  1075→  replayUserMessages: boolean;
  1076→  pendingRequests: Map<string, PendingRequest>;
  1077→  inputClosed: boolean;
  1078→  unexpectedResponseCallback?: (msg: any) => Promise<void>;
  1079→
  1080→  async *read(): AsyncGenerator<ParsedMessage>;
  1081→  async processLine(line: string): Promise<ParsedMessage | undefined>;
  1082→  async write(message: any): Promise<void>;
  1083→  async sendRequest(request: ControlRequestPayload, schema?: ZodSchema, signal?: AbortSignal): Promise<any>;
  1084→  createCanUseTool(onPrompt?: () => void): CanUseToolFn;
  1085→  createHookCallback(callbackId: string, timeout: number): HookCallback;
  1086→  async sendMcpMessage(serverName: string, message: any): Promise<any>;
  1087→  getPendingPermissionRequests(): ControlRequest[];
  1088→}
  1089→```
  1090→
  1091→### `sd1` — WebSocketTransport
  1092→
  1093→```typescript
  1094→class WebSocketTransport {
  1095→  ws: WebSocket | null;
  1096→  url: URL;
  1097→  state: "idle" | "connecting" | "reconnecting" | "connected" | "closing" | "closed";
  1098→  headers: Record<string, string>;
  1099→  sessionId: string | undefined;
  1100→  reconnectAttempts: number;
  1101→  messageBuffer: CircularBuffer;  // capacity: 1000
  1102→
  1103→  async connect(): Promise<void>;
  1104→  sendLine(data: string): boolean;
  1105→  async write(message: any): Promise<void>;
  1106→  handleConnectionError(): void;      // exponential backoff reconnect
  1107→  replayBufferedMessages(lastReceivedId: string): void;
  1108→  startPingInterval(): void;          // 10s ping/pong
  1109→  close(): void;
  1110→  setOnData(cb: (data: string) => void): void;
  1111→  setOnClose(cb: () => void): void;
  1112→}
  1113→```
  1114→
  1115→### `kQA` — HybridTransport (extends sd1)
  1116→
  1117→```typescript
  1118→class HybridTransport extends WebSocketTransport {
  1119→  postUrl: string;  // wss://host/ws/path → https://host/session/path/events
  1120→
  1121→  async write(message: any): Promise<void>;  // HTTP POST with retry
  1122→}
  1123→```
  1124→
  1125→### `LQA` — SdkUrlTransport (extends ad1)
  1126→
  1127→```typescript
  1128→class SdkUrlTransport extends ProcessInputTransport {
  1129→  url: URL;
  1130→  transport: WebSocketTransport | HybridTransport;
  1131→  inputStream: PassThrough;
  1132→
  1133→  constructor(sdkUrl: string, replayStream?: AsyncIterable<string>, replayUserMessages?: boolean);
  1134→  async write(message: any): Promise<void>;  // delegates to transport
  1135→  close(): void;
  1136→}
  1137→```
  1138→
  1139→### `fFA` — DirectConnectWebSocket (Browser Client)
  1140→
  1141→This is the simplest client implementation — useful as a reference for building your own:
  1142→
  1143→```typescript
  1144→class DirectConnectWebSocket {
  1145→  ws: WebSocket | null;
  1146→  config: { wsUrl: string; authToken?: string };
  1147→  callbacks: {
  1148→    onMessage: (msg: any) => void;
  1149→    onConnected?: () => void;
  1150→    onDisconnected?: () => void;
  1151→    onError?: (err: Error) => void;
  1152→    onPermissionRequest: (request: CanUseToolRequest, requestId: string) => void;
  1153→  };
  1154→
  1155→  connect(): void;
  1156→  sendMessage(content: string): boolean;
  1157→  respondToPermissionRequest(requestId: string, response: PermissionResponse): void;
  1158→  sendInterrupt(): void;
  1159→  disconnect(): void;
  1160→  isConnected(): boolean;
  1161→}
  1162→```
  1163→
  1164→**Key implementation details from `fFA`:**
  1165→```javascript
  1166→// Sending a user message
  1167→sendMessage(content) {
  1168→  const msg = JSON.stringify({
  1169→    type: "user",
  1170→    message: { role: "user", content },
  1171→    parent_tool_use_id: null,
  1172→    session_id: ""
  1173→  });
  1174→  this.ws.send(msg);
  1175→}
  1176→
  1177→// Responding to a permission request
  1178→respondToPermissionRequest(requestId, response) {
  1179→  const msg = JSON.stringify({
  1180→    type: "control_response",
  1181→    response: {
  1182→      subtype: "success",
  1183→      request_id: requestId,
  1184→      response: { behavior: response.behavior, ...response }
  1185→    }
  1186→  });
  1187→  this.ws.send(msg);
  1188→}
  1189→
  1190→// Sending an interrupt
  1191→sendInterrupt() {
  1192→  const msg = JSON.stringify({
  1193→    type: "control_request",
  1194→    request_id: crypto.randomUUID(),
  1195→    request: { subtype: "interrupt" }
  1196→  });
  1197→  this.ws.send(msg);
  1198→}
  1199→```
  1200→
  1201→---
  1202→
  1203→## 13. Implementation Guide
  1204→
  1205→### Minimal WebSocket Server (Bun)
  1206→
  1207→```typescript
  1208→const messages: any[] = [];
  1209→
  1210→Bun.serve({
  1211→  port: 8765,
  1212→  fetch(req, server) {
  1213→    if (server.upgrade(req)) return;
  1214→    return new Response("WebSocket server for Claude Code", { status: 200 });
  1215→  },
  1216→  websocket: {
  1217→    open(ws) {
  1218→      console.log("[CONNECTED] Claude Code connected");
  1219→    },
  1220→    message(ws, data) {
  1221→      const lines = data.toString().split("\n").filter(Boolean);
  1222→      for (const line of lines) {
  1223→        const msg = JSON.parse(line);
  1224→        messages.push({ direction: "IN", ...msg });
  1225→
  1226→        // Handle system/init
  1227→        if (msg.type === "system" && msg.subtype === "init") {
  1228→          console.log(`[INIT] session=${msg.session_id} model=${msg.model}`);
  1229→
  1230→          // Send first user message
  1231→          const userMsg = JSON.stringify({
  1232→            type: "user",
  1233→            message: { role: "user", content: "Hello! What can you do?" },
  1234→            parent_tool_use_id: null,
  1235→            session_id: msg.session_id
  1236→          }) + "\n";
  1237→          ws.send(userMsg);
  1238→        }
  1239→
  1240→        // Handle permission requests
  1241→        if (msg.type === "control_request" && msg.request?.subtype === "can_use_tool") {
  1242→          console.log(`[PERMISSION] ${msg.request.tool_name}: ${JSON.stringify(msg.request.input)}`);
  1243→
  1244→          // Auto-approve everything (or add your logic here)
  1245→          const response = JSON.stringify({
  1246→            type: "control_response",
  1247→            response: {
  1248→              subtype: "success",
  1249→              request_id: msg.request_id,
  1250→              response: {
  1251→                behavior: "allow",
  1252→                updatedInput: msg.request.input
  1253→              }
  1254→            }
  1255→          }) + "\n";
  1256→          ws.send(response);
  1257→        }
  1258→
  1259→        // Handle assistant messages
  1260→        if (msg.type === "assistant") {
  1261→          const text = msg.message?.content
  1262→            ?.filter((b: any) => b.type === "text")
  1263→            .map((b: any) => b.text)
  1264→            .join("");
  1265→          console.log(`[ASSISTANT] ${text?.substring(0, 200)}`);
  1266→        }
  1267→
  1268→        // Handle result
  1269→        if (msg.type === "result") {
  1270→          console.log(`[RESULT] ${msg.subtype} | cost=$${msg.total_cost_usd} | turns=${msg.num_turns}`);
  1271→        }
  1272→
  1273→        // Ignore keep_alive
  1274→        if (msg.type === "keep_alive") return;
  1275→      }
  1276→    },
  1277→    close(ws) {
  1278→      console.log("[DISCONNECTED]");
  1279→    }
  1280→  }
  1281→});
  1282→
  1283→console.log("WebSocket server running on ws://localhost:8765");
  1284→```
  1285→
  1286→### Launch Claude Code
  1287→
  1288→```bash
  1289→claude --sdk-url ws://localhost:8765 \
  1290→       --print \
  1291→       --output-format stream-json \
  1292→       --input-format stream-json \
  1293→       --verbose \
  1294→       -p ""
  1295→```
  1296→
  1297→### Building a Full Controller
  1298→
  1299→To build a production controller on top of this protocol:
  1300→
  1301→1. **WebSocket Server**: Accept connections, handle NDJSON messages
  1302→2. **Message Router**: Dispatch by `type` field (system, assistant, result, control_request, etc.)
  1303→3. **Permission Handler**: Implement policy for `can_use_tool` requests (auto-approve, deny, or prompt user)
  1304→4. **Session Manager**: Track session_id, support resume via `--resume`
  1305→5. **Multi-Turn**: Send additional `user` messages after each `result`
  1306→6. **Streaming**: Process `stream_event` messages for real-time output
  1307→7. **Error Handling**: Handle `result` with `is_error: true`, connection drops, reconnection
  1308→8. **Lifecycle**: Use `initialize` control_request for hooks/MCP, `interrupt` to abort
  1309→
  1310→### Key Differences from the Filesystem Inbox Protocol
  1311→
  1312→| Aspect | Filesystem Inbox | WebSocket Protocol |
  1313→|--------|-----------------|-------------------|
  1314→| Transport | JSON files in `~/.claude/teams/` | NDJSON over WebSocket |
  1315→| Permissions | Not natively routed through inbox | Full `can_use_tool` flow |
  1316→| Latency | Polling (500ms) | Real-time |
  1317→| Multi-turn | Send message → poll for response | Send message → stream response |
  1318→| Streaming | Not supported | `stream_event` messages |
  1319→| Session control | Limited (mode, shutdown) | Full (model, thinking, MCP, rewind) |
  1320→| Dependency | Teammate mode required | Standalone (`--print` mode) |
  1321→
  1322→---
  1323→
  1324→## Appendix: Permission Mode Reference
  1325→
  1326→| Mode | `can_use_tool` sent? | Behavior |
  1327→|------|---------------------|----------|
  1328→| `default` | Yes (when rules don't resolve) | Normal flow |
  1329→| `acceptEdits` | Yes (for non-edit tools) | Auto-approves file edits |
  1330→| `bypassPermissions` | **Never** | Everything auto-approved locally |
  1331→| `plan` | Yes (limited) | Read-only exploration mode |
  1332→| `delegate` | N/A | Restricted to coordination tools only |
  1333→| `dontAsk` | **Never** | Auto-denies unresolved permissions |
  1334→
  1335→---
  1336→
  1337→## Appendix: Shared Types
  1338→
  1339→```typescript
  1340→type PermissionMode = "default" | "acceptEdits" | "bypassPermissions" | "plan" | "delegate" | "dontAsk";
  1341→
  1342→type HookEvent =
  1343→  | "PreToolUse" | "PostToolUse" | "PostToolUseFailure"
  1344→  | "Notification" | "UserPromptSubmit"
  1345→  | "SessionStart" | "SessionEnd"
  1346→  | "Stop" | "SubagentStart" | "SubagentStop"
  1347→  | "PreCompact" | "PermissionRequest"
  1348→  | "Setup" | "TeammateIdle" | "TaskCompleted";
  1349→
  1350→type ContentBlock =
  1351→  | { type: "text"; text: string }
  1352→  | { type: "tool_use"; id: string; name: string; input: Record<string, unknown> }
  1353→  | { type: "tool_result"; tool_use_id: string; content: string | ContentBlock[]; is_error?: boolean }
  1354→  | { type: "thinking"; thinking: string; budget_tokens?: number };
  1355→```
  1356→

